cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE 

This paper deals with wireless communication networks and optimization of resources such as time, frequency, and power. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves relay networks, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of a hybrid relay node and the consideration of processing costs suggest the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves simulations, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
